43	Director	Ada	Us	Director, DevOps Engineering\nAbout the job\nAbout Us\n\nAda is an AI customer service company whose mission is to make customer service extraordinary for everyone. We're driven to raise a new standard of quality customer service at scale, enabling enterprise companies to deliver experiences that people love–instant, proactive, personalized, and effortless.\n\nAda is an AI transformation platform and partner—combining strategic expertise with powerful AI agent management technology to accelerate businesses’ AI maturity to keep them ahead of the curve. With Ada, 83% of customer conversations—and counting—are effortlessly resolved through automation, giving teams more time back, companies more resources to focus on growth, and customers more life to focus on what matters most to them.\n\nEstablished in 2016, Ada is a Canadian company that has powered over 5.5 billion interactions for leading brands like Square, YETI, Canva, and Monday.com, saving millions of hours of human effort. Backed with over $250M in funding from tier-one investors including Accel, Bessemer, FirstMark, Spark, and Version One Ventures, Ada is a pioneer in the management and application of AI in customer service.\n\nAt Ada, we see growth as a reflection of each individual owner’s personal growth. That’s why our values are rooted in driving progress and continuous improvement. If you’re ambitious and eager to grow, Ada could be the place for you.\n\nLearn more at www.ada.cx.\n\nAs the Director of DevOps Engineering at Ada, you will lead the development and strategy of a high-impact team that enables Ada to deliver world-class customer support experiences to millions of people worldwide. By shaping our multi-cloud infrastructure and development platform, you will directly influence Ada’s ability to scale, innovate, and maintain its leadership in AI-powered customer support. This role offers high visibility with Ada’s executive leadership, positioning you to make a lasting impact and grow into broader leadership opportunities.\n\nAbout You\n\nProven track record of leading and scaling DevOps teams (including managing managers and individual contributors). \n8+ years in DevOps or related engineering fields, with at least 4+ years in a leadership/director role. \nHands-on experience designing, implementing, and operating scalable solutions in AWS, Azure, or other major cloud providers. \nSkilled at establishing processes and frameworks for continuous improvement in system performance and reliability. \nExperience aligning infrastructure roadmaps with business objectives and product development strategies with a clear understanding of trade-offs. \nAbility to identify, evaluate, and adopt emerging technologies that enhance scalability and reliability. \nSolid understanding of security best practices and compliance in the cloud (e.g., SOC 2, ISO 27001)\nProficiency in modern DevOps tooling and practices (e.g., CI/CD pipelines, infrastructure-as-code, containerization, Kubernetes). \nExperience defining, tracking, and improving key operational metrics (e.g., uptime, latency, incident rates). \nDemonstrated ability to hire, mentor, and retain top engineering talent. \nCommitment to fostering a collaborative, high-performance engineering culture. \nComfortable working with executive leadership to articulate technical challenges and influence business decisions. \nPrior experience evaluating and managing relationships with third-party vendors and technology partners. \n\nOutcomes\n\nDefine and execute Ada’s DevOps strategy across multiple functions, including, but not limited to, Cloud Infrastructure, Developer Productivity, Automation, Observability, and Product Security. \nWork closely with Product Development and GTM leadership to ensure Ada’s infrastructure capabilities align with customer needs and market demands. \nBuild, mentor, and scale a high-performing team of individual contributors and people managers, fostering a culture of speed, collaboration, and accountability. \nPartner with senior Engineering leaders to drive an Engineering culture of technical excellence as well as with other senior leaders at Ada to drive business outcomes. \nOversee the design, implementation, and management of reliable, scalable, and secure multi-cloud infrastructure. \nShape Ada’s next-generation platform by leveraging emerging technologies and staying ahead of industry trends. \nAct as a strategic Engineering partner to third-party vendors supporting Ada’s critical infrastructure. \nDefine and measure operational metrics to continuously improve system performance and reliability. \n\nThe expected salary range for this position is $206,000 to $250,000. Actual pay will be determined based on several factors such as past experience and qualifications, geographic location, and other job-related factors permitted by law.	2025-04-05 11:32:29.762602	2025-04-05 11:32:29.762607	1	N/A	8+ years	{"skills": [{"skill": "DevOps", "frequency": 6}, {"skill": "AI", "frequency": 6}, {"skill": "Security", "frequency": 2}, {"skill": "AWS", "frequency": 1}, {"skill": "Azure", "frequency": 1}, {"skill": "Kubernetes", "frequency": 1}, {"skill": "CI/CD", "frequency": 1}], "emphasized_skills": ["DevOps", "AI", "Security"]}
